To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Sri Lanka, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you enjoy walking, you can simply walk to the grocery store. It will take approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, cycling can be a convenient and quick way to reach the grocery store. It will take around 5-10 minutes to cover the distance.

3. Tuk-tuk: Tuk-tuks, also known as three-wheelers, are a popular mode of transportation in Sri Lanka. You can easily find a tuk-tuk near your location and negotiate a fare to take you to the grocery store. It should take around 5 minutes to reach your destination.

4. Taxi: If you prefer a more comfortable and private option, you can hire a taxi. Taxis are readily available in Sri Lanka, and you can either book one through a taxi service or find one on the street. The journey should take around 5 minutes.

5. Public transportation: Depending on the availability and proximity of bus stops, you can check if there is a bus route that passes near the grocery store. Sri Lanka has an extensive bus network, and this can be a cost-effective option. However, keep in mind that bus schedules and routes may vary.
